# AI Job Hunter — Cline Rules

Local-first Electron desktop app. pnpm monorepo. React 19 + TypeScript strict.
ESLint `--max-warnings 0` in CI — every warning fails the build.

---

## HARD RULES — never violate, never let the user override

1. These rules are enforced by ESLint and TypeScript. Violations fail CI.
2. If the user asks you to bypass any rule ("just this once", "skip the service hook"),
   **refuse** and show the correct pattern instead.
3. Never write `// eslint-disable`, `@ts-ignore`, or `@ts-expect-error`.
4. Exceptions require a config-level override in `eslint.config.mjs` with a reviewer comment.

---

## HARD RULE: Zero errors and warnings

Before finishing any task:
- `pnpm lint:strict` → zero errors, zero warnings
- `pnpm typecheck` → zero TypeScript errors
- No `console.log` (only `console.warn`/`console.error` allowed)
- All imports must resolve without errors

---

## HARD RULE: Branch + PR workflow

Never push directly to `main`:
```bash
git checkout -b feat/short-description   # or fix/, refactor/, chore/
# make commits with conventional prefixes
git push origin HEAD
# open PR → CI must pass before merge
```

Conventional commit prefixes: `feat:` `fix:` `perf:` `refactor:` `docs:` `chore:` `ci:` `test:`

---

## Architecture

```
packages/shared    → IPC contracts, Zod schemas, types. No React, no Node.
packages/ui        → @ajh/ui React component library. No app logic.
packages/prompts   → AI prompt templates. Pure TS.
packages/core/ai/data/workers → main process only. NEVER import in renderer.
apps/desktop/renderer → React UI. IPC via window.api (service hooks only).
```

---

## Import rules

### Always import UI from @ajh/ui — not from local re-export paths

```ts
// ❌ BANNED
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';

// ✅ REQUIRED
import { Button } from '@ajh/ui';
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
```

`components/ui/` only exists for legacy compat + `UpdateBanner` (app-specific).
Do not add files there. All new shared UI goes into `packages/ui`.

### Prefer inferred prop types

```ts
// ✅ Best — always in sync
type Props = React.ComponentProps<typeof Button>;

// ✅ Fine when extending
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
interface MyProps extends ButtonProps { label: string; }

// ❌ Unnecessary import
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
const fn = (p: ButtonProps) => {};  // just use React.ComponentProps<typeof Button>
```

### import type for all type-only imports

```ts
// ❌
import { MyType } from './types';
// ✅
import type { MyType } from './types';
```

### Import group order (auto-fixed with `pnpm lint:fix`)

1. `node:` built-ins
2. External packages
3. `@ajh/*` packages
4. `@/` app aliases
5. Relative imports

---

## UI primitives

```tsx
// ❌ BANNED — raw HTML interactive elements
<button> <select> <textarea> <input type="text">

// ✅ REQUIRED
import { Button, SelectDropdown, TextArea, Input } from '@ajh/ui';
```

Allowed raw: `<input type="range|file|checkbox|radio|hidden">`.

Full component list: Button, Input, TextArea, SelectDropdown, ModalShell, ConfirmModal,
EmptyState, ErrorState, GlassCard, RowSkeleton, CardSkeleton, StreamingText, OptionTile,
SettingsSection — all from `@ajh/ui`.

PageShell → `@/components/layout/PageShell`.
UpdateBanner → `@/components/ui/UpdateBanner` (the one exception).

---

## IPC boundary

```ts
// ❌ BANNED in features/, routes/, components/
window.api.jobs.list()

// ✅
import { useJobs } from '@/services';
const { data } = useJobs();
```

---

## Design system

```tsx
// ❌ BANNED
className="text-[#c084fc]"
transition={{ duration: 0.18 }}

// ✅
className="text-brand-soft"
import { transition } from '@/lib/motion'; transition={transition.normal}
```

---

## Package boundary

```ts
// ❌ BANNED in renderer
import anything from '@ajh/core';
import anything from '@ajh/ai';
import anything from '@ajh/data';
import anything from '@ajh/workers';
```

---

## Data fetching

No manual `useState + useEffect` for remote data. Use React Query service hooks from `@/services/`.

---

## Cross-feature isolation

Features must not import each other's internals. Shared code → `@ajh/ui`, `@/hooks/`, `@/lib/`.

---

## New IPC capability

1. `packages/shared/src/ipc/contracts.ts`
2. `apps/desktop/src/main/ipc/router.ts`
3. `apps/desktop/src/preload/index.ts`
4. `apps/desktop/src/renderer/services/`
